<subSubSection lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="229" pageId="5" pageNumber="228" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="5.[794,1400,1801,2081]" pageId="5" pageNumber="228">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[794,904,1801,1825]" pageId="5" pageNumber="228">Diagnosis</emphasis>
: This species is characterised by the rounded propodeum with weak sculpture. A special feature of the males is the shape of the penis valves, that in dorsal view are strikingly constricted in the middle. Also in the other terminalia, the ground plan morphology of the subgenus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="FABRICIUS" authorityYear="1793" box="[901,986,1961,1985]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Hylaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="228" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[901,986,1961,1985]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="228">Hylaeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is modified in a specific manner. The females can be easily recognised by the fungiform spot on the anterior margin of the clypeus. Both sexes are remarkably pilose.
</paragraph>
